    <release version="0.2.7" date="2023-09-07">
      <description>
        <p>Reduces the flatpak package size and updates fava.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Maintenance: Reduces the flatpak package size by cleaning up the blueprint compiler after building.</li>
          <li>Maintenance: Updates fava as well as other python package dependencies.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.6" date="2023-08-27">
      <description>
        <p>Better desktop integration.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>New feature: This release improves the app's integration with the GNOME desktop. The Fava Desktop app is now associated with *.beancount files, allowing users to choose "Open with..." and to then choose "Fava" in GNOME Files.</li>
          <li>New feature: It is now possible to open beancount files in favagtk straight from GNOME Files (or any other file explorer, for that matter).</li>
          <li>Maintenance: Updates to GNOME 44, updates fava and beancount.</li>
          <li>Maintenance> Updates various dependencies including blueprint and python libraries.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.5" date="2023-03-05">
      <description>
        <p>Maintenance release</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Updates python dependencies.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.4" date="2022-12-18">
      <description>
        <p>Maintenance release</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Updates python dependencies.</li>
          <li>Configured gitlab CI to automatically submit merge requests with updated dependencies.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.3" date="2022-11-04">
      <description>
        <p>Maintenance release</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Updated fava to version 1.23.1, and updated other dependencies as well.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.2" date="2022-10-15">
      <description>
        <p>Maintenance release</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Updated fava to version 1.23, and updated other dependencies as well.</li>
          <li>Updated to GNOME 43.</li>
          <li>Faster and simpler build process.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.1" date="2022-08-20">
      <description>
        <p>Maintenance release</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed a bug where included beancount files failed to load: Widened the flatpak sandbox permissions for accessing the users' file system.</li>
          <li>Fixed a bug where the UI froze when users clicked the file-open button inside the recent files popover.</li>
          <li>Fixed a sporadic crash when opening a beancount file. The crash was due to a concurrency issue when favagtk checks if and when fava's server becomes available.</li>
          <li>Fixed a bug where the window could not be closed. This happened because of an exception trying to save the last-opened beancount file.</li>
          <li>Updated fava to version 1.22, and updated other dependencies as well.</li>
          <li>Optimized development builds: Faster build times locally and in gitlab-ci.</li>
          <li>Adds ARM (aarch64) builds, untested because I don't have an ARM linux test device.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.2.0" date="2022-06-18">
      <description>
        <p>Full rewrite using GTK4</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Visual refresh using GKT4</li>
          <li>Using GNOME Builder, flatpak and meson as primary build system</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>
